May 8 at 1:58 PM ¬∑

Today would have been Graduation day for the Fort Osage High School class of 2020. While we are sad we can not celebrate their graduation, we have a special week of activities planned to honor seniors on social media. Today, Mr. Moore, Fort Osage High School principal, has a special message for our seniors and their families. Watch our Facebook page each day for special video messages, challenges, and we are super excited about a surprise that will run May 18th-24th, but you will have to just wait a few more days before we share that surprise!

To the FOHS Class of 2020 you have been an amazing group of students. We hope that you will enjoy this week dedicated just to celebrating you! #FortProud #FOHSClassof2020

shared_text:
Fort Osage School District
February 3 at 11:04 AM ¬∑

Fort Osage, along with other Kansas City metro school districts, are cancelling classes for Wednesday, February 5th. This decision was made due to the number of students and staff who plan to be absent from school to attend the Chiefs Super Bowl celebration. As in 2015 when the Royals won the World Series, there is a concern over the number of substitutes that are needed and the quality of the education day with so many students absent.

Our Fort Discovery program will remain open normal hours for families enrolled. Families will need to report to Blue Hills Elementary School and need to bring breakfast and lunch for their child.

Sports are on as scheduled for Wednesday. DECA and Skills USA competitions have been rescheduled. The CTC open house has been rescheduled for February 6th.

Reminder there is no school on Tuesday, February 4 for staff professional development.

The last day of school is Friday, May 22.

shared_text:
Fort Osage School District
August 1, 2018 at 11:23 AM ¬∑

All families must provide proof of residency in the school district each year. For the 2018-19 school year, that is being completed online with our new enrollment system. You should have received an email with a user specific link to enroll your students and upload your residency information. If you did not receive that email, you can contact fo_onlinereg@fortosage.net.

Once you have completed the enrollment and residency process, your students will begin to receive their teacher's name or schedule starting later this week or early next week.

If you need help completing this process, you can come to our schools on the following dates and times

K-6th grade families today until 4:00 p.m. or August 2 from 11:00-7:00
7-8th grade families on August 7 from 10:00-6:00
11-12th grade families on August 1: 9:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. and 5:00-7:00 p.m.
9-10th grade families on August 2: 9:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. and 5:00-7:00 p.m.
All Fort Osage High School students August 3: 9:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m.

post_text:
Seniors and guests going to Project Grad......

*Be at the Senior parking lot by 9:45PM on Tuesday, May 8th wearing your Project Grad shirt.

*You may bring swimsuit, towel, hair brush, phone, phone charger and earbuds (Students that are driving to school may bring their keys and id, no purses. You are responsible for all these items). All of this should be in the clear plastic bag you received your shirt in.

*Bags will be checked before boarding the bus.

*You do not need money, food or drink.

*Food and drink are not permitted on the bus.

*Senior and senior guest must board the bus together.

Congratulations!

If you would like to tepee a yard within the Fort Osage School District boundaries, please fill out
the information below. Your request will be fulfilled within 2 weeks. Tepees are picked up 48-96
hours after being set up. Our tepee-ing is done in good spirits to show school pride and is not
meant to be malicious. The tepees are precious property to us, and we want to keep them in
top shape so all can enjoy.
